  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nepal Terai Flood Emergency Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	The flood and landslides caused after the incessant rainfall since 11th of August 2017 have deteriorated the condition of more than 34 districts across the country. 
&#x2022;	Major cities in the Terai Plains was flooded and inundated, over 80% area had been covered by water.
&#x2022;	According to the latest update circulated by the government (MOHA) altogether 143 people have been dead, 43 injured while 30 people have gone missing. 
&#x2022;	Additionally, 91,400 families have been temporarily displaced, 65,000 houses have been destroyed and approximately, 1.7 million individuals have been affected by this catastrophe.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	This project is distributing shelter items, bedding sets, kitchen kits, and dry food rations (enough for a family of 5 for two weeks) to 620 households affected by the flooding in Musahari village in Sunsari (eastern region) and Gaushala, Balawa, Bhangaha and Matihani municipalities in Mahottari (Central region)</narrative>
  </description>
